name: 2,3,4,5-tetrafluorobenzamide

However, the presence of multiple fluorines can cause steric hindrance which slightly reduces their individual contributions to the overall melting point (approx. -2°C per additional fluorine after the first). As there are four fluorine atoms, we will consider the cumulative addition of three after the first with the steric hindrance factor: +20°C for the first F, and then +18°C per each of the other three Fs.
